article.description: Camren Wynter had a career-high 31 points as Drexel defeated Princeton 82-76 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Wynter scores 31 to carry Drexel over Princeton 82-76
article.linkText: Wynter scores 31 to carry Drexel over Princeton 82-76
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Camren Wynter had a career-high 31 points as Drexel defeated Princeton 82-76 on Wednesday night. Wynter shot 13 for 16 from the floor. James Butler had 18 points, 12 rebounds and four blocks for Drexel (5-4), which earned its fifth straight home victory. Jaelin Llewellyn scored a career-high 28 points for the Tigers (1-6). Tosan Evbuomwan, Richmond Aririguzoh and Ryan Schwieger had 10 points apiece. Drexel matches up against La Salle at home on Saturday. Princeton plays Monmouth at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
